article.description: — Jaylen Murray scored 18 points as Saint Peter's beat Fairleigh Dickinson 77-63 on Sunday.
article.headline: Murray nets 18, Saint Peter's tops Fairleigh Dickinson 77-63
article.linkText: Murray nets 18, Saint Peter's tops Fairleigh Dickinson 77-63
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- — Jaylen Murray scored 18 points as Saint Peter's beat Fairleigh Dickinson 77-63 on Sunday. Murray shot 4 for 8 from beyond the arc and 6 of 6 from the free throw line for the Peacocks (4-2). Latrell Reid scored 11 points and added six rebounds and eight assists. Isiah Dasher finished 4 of 8 from the field to finish with 10 points. The Knights (3-5) were led by Heru Bligen, who posted 16 points. Grant Singleton added 14 points for Fairleigh Dickinson. Demetre Roberts also had 13 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
